    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Aligning Your Org to Accounting and ERP Systems\n Defining Rules and Treatments\n GL Rules and GL Treatments\n Define Your Invoicing Setup with Billing Rules\n Tax Rules and Treatments\n Configuring Your Revenue Recognition Rules\n Dynamic Invoice Plans\n Setting Up Usage Products\n Guidelines for Using Salesforce Billing with Multicurrency Enabled\n Billing Account Fields\n Automation in Salesforce Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nDefining Rules and Treatments\n\nSalesforce Billing uses rules and treatments to group records for evaluation and take action on specific records within that group based on matching values. After Salesforce Billing performs certain actions, it evaluates all records that share the same rule and applies general changes to those records based on the rule’s settings. The rule also contains treatment records, which allow Salesforce Billing to apply more specific changes. Salesforce Billing applies a treatment to one of the groups’s records only if the record and the treatment have the same legal entity.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: All Salesforce Billing Editions\n\nRules are initially defined on the product record and on legal entities.\n\nGL Rules and GL Treatments\nGeneral ledger rules define how Salesforce Billing records transactional data to your finance books.\nDefine Your Invoicing Setup with Billing Rules\nBilling rules define how your order product produces an invoice line during an invoicing process.\nTax Rules and Treatments\nTax rules and their treatments define how Salesforce Billing processes tax for your transactions.\nConfiguring Your Revenue Recognition Rules\nRevenue recognition rules define whether Salesforce Billing creates a revenue schedule for an invoiced order product or invoice line.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
